{
  "doc_id": "8592",
  "text": "Some studies specify the lines of chemotherapy administered, but our study does not. In Davidoff et al. [CITATION_1] , 23% of all patients were treated in the first line with a platinum doublet, and 23% were treated in the second line with a platinum doublet. That finding leads to the conclusion that a doublet-based regimen is more commonly prescribed-a conclusion supported by a recent abstract in which platinum-based doublets were shown to be superior to single-agent therapy in the treatment of elderly patients more than 70 years of age [CITATION_2] . That study found greater treatment-related toxicity in elderly patients without greater treatment-related mortality [CITATION_3] .",
